This will likely be a common scenario, because there is a significant delay between clicking the start icon, and seeing any response.

Build log shows:

{noformat}
23-Jan-2008 15:20:41	 Manual build triggered by ahempel
23-Jan-2008 15:20:48	 Manual build rquest ignored. Plan is currently busy (may already be building)
{noformat}

From BSP-499,

{quote}
I have some build plans under one project that I want to move to a new Project. But there is no interface for just creating an empty project, so I had to create a dummy build plan to get the destination project. After that I could move my plans to that project and remove the dummy plan.
{quote}

From [Bamboo Forum post|http://forums.atlassian.com/thread.jspa?threadID=21907&tstart=0]:

{quote}
we have observed that this wizard behaves rather like a 'Bulk Set Plan Permissions Wizard' in that it seems to completely ignore the existing permissions of the involved plans and always presents the user with the same default permissions instead (as shown here in Screenshot 2). 

Our situation is that we have several plans with identical but non-default permissions (e.g. we have explicitly set permissions for several groups). When we now want to perform a single identical change on the permissions for all the plans with the BEPP wizard we are forced to re-establish the current permissions before we can perform the change - which may take almost as long as performing the single change on all the plans individually.

We would have expected that this kind of wizard works incrementally (which implies that it must be capable of dealing with the situation where the plans have non-identical permissions) and changes only permissions that have been explicitly edited.
{quote}
